programme.title: Saudi and Trans: Eden's Final Message
programme.desc: In March 2023, a post went viral on Twitter - the 'Final Message' from Eden Knight, a young Saudi transgender woman. It was viewed over 35 million times. It laid bare Eden's journey from the US back to Saudi Arabia and the betrayal she claimed to have suffered. BBC Eye investigates the events that led up to Eden's death and those she claims were responsible for her return to Saudi Arabia where she tragically took her own life. Many theories surrounded the circumstances of her death. Eden claimed she had been encouraged to return to Saudi Arabia from the US by a lawyer, whom she never fully identified. Investigative journalist Katy Ling sets out to find him and the other individuals mentioned in Eden's 'Final Message'. Eden had been living in the US, hoping to start a new life. She was studying computer science on a scholarship funded by the Saudi government. In 2022 she started her transition. Knowing her family would never accept her, Eden made the difficult decision to cut ties with them and to claim asylum in the US. While seeking asylum, Eden was contacted by an American businessman offering help. He introduced her to a lawyer in Washington DC. Text messages and social media posts reveal that Eden believed the lawyer was assisting her with her asylum application, but just two months later, she was on a plane back to Saudi Arabia with him. Using geolocation data, animation, social media posts, and text messages from Eden's friends, the team from the BBC World Service reconstructs the final months of Eden?s life. In Atlanta, Katy meets Eden's closest friends, who share the fears that drove Eden?s decision to leave her family behind and the hope she had for her future.

programme.desc: La casa de Mamen se va a convertir en el set de un anuncio de galletas, pero a ltima hora, los de la agencia cambian de idea y deciden que la cocina de los Cuesta es menos artificial y que lo van a grabar all.

programme.title: Aqu no hay quien viva - T5, E10: rase Un Funeral Con Sorpresa
programme.desc: El da del funeral de Paloma radio-patio prepara una programacin especial para cubrir el evento. Mientras tanto, Juan, Isabel y Jos Miguel, adems de algunos de los vecinos, acuden al tanatorio donde Paloma va a ser incinerada.

programme.title: Chicas malas

programme.title: Young Winston

While working as a journalist, he travels to Africa to report on the Boer Wars, an assignment that leads to his incarceration in a prison camp. He escapes from captivity and returns to England to begin a political career. Directed by Richard Attenborough and starring Simon Ward, Anthony Hopkins, Anne Bancroft and Robert Shaw

programme.title: Operation Petticoat
programme.desc: A Second World War submarine captain tries to restore his crippled vessel to its former glory, but is thwarted by his first officer, who has invited a party of nurses, children and an expectant mother on board. Mayhem ensues as the skipper struggles to rein in the female influence on ship protocol. Comedy, starring Cary Grant, Tony Curtis and Joan O'Brien

programme.title: We Live in Time Interview Special

programme.title: Bend It Like Beckham
programme.desc: An English schoolgirl tries to hide her passion for football from her strict Indian parents, knowing they disapprove of her tomboyish love of the game. However, when a semi-professional player sees her in action, she is offered a place on a team, forcing her to come up with a complex plan to keep her sporting career under wraps. Comedy, with Parminder Nagra, Keira Knightley, Jonathan Rhys Meyers, Juliet Stevenson and Shaznay Lewis

programme.title: Bad Boys for Life
programme.desc: Isabel Aretas, the widow of crime lord Benito, escapes from a Mexican prison with the help of her son, Armando. She sends him to Miami to recover the stash of money his father had hidden, as well as assassinating those responsible for his dad's arrest and eventual death in prison. She demands that Armando kill Miami detective Mike Lowrey last. Action sequel, starring Will Smith, Martin Lawrence, Paola Nunez and Vanessa Hudgens

programme.title: Die Hard
programme.desc: New York cop John McClane visits Los Angeles to see his family over the Christmas holiday. Stopping off at his wife's place of work, he realises armed men have taken over the building and are holding the corporation's staff to ransom - and only he has the ability to fight back. Action thriller, starring Bruce Willis, Alan Rickman and Bonnie Bedelia

programme.title: Jungleland
programme.desc: Two brothers try to escape their circumstances by travelling across America for a no-holds-barred boxing match that becomes a fight for their lives. Director Max Winkler's drama, starring Charlie Hunnam, Jack O'Connell and Jonathan Majors

programme.title: The Long Ships
programme.desc: A Viking warrior steals a ship and leads his crew in search of a legendary bell, rumoured to be three times the size of a man and made of solid gold. But they have reckoned without the ambition of the king of the Moors, who captures the Vikings and intends to use them to find the prize for himself. Adventure, starring Richard Widmark, Sidney Poitier, Rosanna Schiaffino, Russ Tamblyn and Lionel Jeffries

programme.title: An Affair to Remember
programme.desc: Love blossoms on the high seas for a playboy bachelor and a former nightclub singer during a transatlantic cruise. When the liner comes into dock at New York, they agree to wait for six months and then meet again at the Empire State Building, hoping to prove to each other their relationship is more than a shipboard affair. Romantic drama, starring Cary Grant, Deborah Kerr, Cathleen Nesbitt, Richard Denning and Neva Patterson.

programme.title: Anzio
programme.desc: An American war correspondent joins Allied troops in 1944 as they prepare for their landing in Italy. A strategic blunder by their commanding officer gives German forces time to reinforce the area, leaving the reporter caught up in one of the campaign's fiercest battles. Second World War drama, starring Robert Mitchum, Peter Falk, Arthur Kennedy, Robert Ryan and Earl Holliman

programme.title: Independence Day
programme.desc: A fleet of huge flying saucers launches a devastating and unprovoked attack on Earth. As survivors try to flee the seemingly unstoppable alien invaders, the courageous US president, an ace pilot and a computer genius come up with a plan to take the fight to the enemy and save the human race. Roland Emmerich's sci-fi adventure, starring Will Smith, Bill Pullman, Jeff Goldblum, Mary McDonnell, Randy Quaid, Robert Loggia and Harry Connick Jr

programme.title: The Father
programme.desc: An old man gradually succumbing to dementia drives off a succession of caregivers, to the frustration of his daughter, who is contemplating starting a new life in Paris. As his condition steadily worsens, he finds his perspective of his surroundings, the events of his past and future, and even the passage of time itself becoming painfully distorted. Drama, starring an Oscar-winning Anthony Hopkins alongside Olivia Colman, Imogen Poots and Rufus Sewell

programme.title: Fury
programme.desc: A veteran American sergeant leads a tank crew on one final dangerous mission in the last months of the Second World War. The assignment takes the soldiers behind enemy lines and into battle with overwhelming enemy forces, while the presence of an inexperienced new recruit in the team raises tension. Drama, starring Brad Pitt and Shia LaBeouf

programme.title: Shayda
programme.desc: A woman struggles to start afresh after fleeing her abusive marriage. Writer and director Noora Niasari's drama, starring Zar Amir Ebrahimi and Leah Purcell. In English and Persian, with English subtitles

programme.title: Gideon of Scotland Yard
programme.desc: Police inspector George Gideon experiences an eventful day's work. He learns one of his detectives has accepted bribes, goes on the trail of a murderous maniac and tracks a woman suspected of robbery. He also helps foil a bank heist and gets off on the wrong foot with an eager young constable. John Ford's drama, starring Jack Hawkins, Dianne Foster, Anna Lee and Anna Massey

programme.title: 3:10 to Yuma
programme.desc: A farmer in need of money agrees to guard a notorious outlaw until the train arrives to transport him to jail. Meanwhile, the pair are holed up in a hotel, where his prisoner plays mind games with him - and the villain's cohorts are waiting outside ready to engineer an escape. Western adapted from a novel by Elmore Leonard, with Van Heflin, Glenn Ford, Felicia Farr and Leora Dana

programme.title: Anastasia
programme.desc: In 1920s Paris, exiled Russians claim they have found the daughter of the last Tsar, who was originally believed to have been killed with the rest of her family. She is taken into the care of a General and groomed until she can convince Anastasia's cousin Prince Paul that she is genuinely the tsarina and inherit a fortune. Historical drama, starring an Oscar-winning Ingrid Bergman, and Yul Brynner

programme.title: Little Women
programme.desc: Four sisters are raised by their strong-willed mother while their father is away fighting in the American Civil War. Although one yearns to become a writer and another dreams of being married, the girls remain firmly united as the family steers a course through hard times and tragic events. Period drama, based on Louisa May Alcott's novel, with Winona Ryder, Susan Sarandon, Claire Danes, Samantha Mathis and Kirsten Dunst

programme.title: 13 Going on 30
programme.desc: A 13-year-old girl wishes she could skip the misery of growing up and become an adult overnight. However, the next day she wakes up to find 17 years have mysteriously passed and she is now a successful magazine editor approaching her 30th birthday - and her new life is just as hard to cope with as her old one. Romantic comedy, starring Jennifer Garner, Mark Ruffalo, Christa B Allen and Andy Serkis

programme.title: Vesper
programme.desc: Thirteen-year-old Vesper and her paralysed father struggle to survive on the desolate outskirts of a gated city, until they meet a mysterious woman who promises to change their lives. Sci-fi adventure, starring Raffiella Chapman, Eddie Marsan, Rosy McEwan and Richard Brake

programme.title: The Running Man
programme.desc: A helicopter pilot is framed for the murder of starving civilians - and ends up being forced to take part in a brutal TV game show in which a succession of gadget-wielding killers hunt him on the streets of Los Angeles.
